# Installation Guide

## Prerequisites

- Go 1.21 or later
- GCC compiler (required for SQLite3 CGO bindings)

### macOS
```bash
brew install go
# GCC comes with Xcode Command Line Tools
xcode-select --install
```

### Linux (Debian/Ubuntu)
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install golang-go gcc
```

### Linux (RHEL/Fedora)
```bash
sudo dnf install golang gcc
```

## Installation Methods

### Method 1: Build from Source

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone <repository-url>
cd cariskscore

# Build the binary
go build -o cariskscore ./cmd/cariskscore

# Optionally, move to PATH
sudo mv cariskscore /usr/local/bin/
```

### Method 2: Go Install

```bash
# Install directly from source
cd cariskscore
go install ./cmd/cariskscore

# Binary will be in $GOPATH/bin or ~/go/bin
```

### Method 3: Download Pre-built Binary

Check the releases page for pre-built binaries for your platform.

## Post-Installation

### Verify Installation

```bash
./cariskscore --help
```

### Initialize Database

```bash
# Index Certificate Authorities
./cariskscore index

# Compute security scores
./cariskscore score
```

### Database Location

By default, data is stored at `~/.cariskscore/cariskscore.db`

To use a custom location:
```bash
export CARISKSCORE_DB=/path/to/custom/db.sqlite
```

## Troubleshooting

### CGO Errors

If you see errors about CGO or sqlite3:

```bash
# Ensure GCC is installed
gcc --version

# Try building with CGO explicitly enabled
CGO_ENABLED=1 go build -o cariskscore ./cmd/cariskscore
```

### Permission Errors

If database creation fails:

```bash
# Ensure ~/.cariskscore directory exists and is writable
mkdir -p ~/.cariskscore
chmod 755 ~/.cariskscore
```

### Network Issues

The tool requires internet access to:
- Download CCADB data (index command)
- Query crt.sh API (search command)

Ensure firewall rules allow outbound HTTPS connections.

## Uninstallation

```bash
# Remove binary
rm /usr/local/bin/cariskscore

# Remove database and config
rm -rf ~/.cariskscore
```

